<SUMMARY>
SUMMARY:

 The Agricultural Stabilization and Conservation Service (ASCS) is proposing to increase fees charged warehousemen
for licensing and inspection services under the United States Warehouse Act (USWA) for grain, tobacco, wool, dry
beans, nuts, syrup, and cottonseed. In addition, an initial schedule of fees for cotton warehousemen is being added.
Future fee changes will be announced by a notice in the 

Federal Register

 prior to July 1, to be effective October 1 of each year, when such changes have been determined to be necessary.

 

</SUMMARY>
