Warehouse license fees for cotton, grain, tobacco, wool, dry beans, nut, syrup, and cottonseed are proposed to be
increased from $50 to $65. 

Service license fees issued to individuals and entities to inspect, sample, grade, classify, or weigh commodities
are proposed to be increased from $20 to $26. 



